51.4	Libretto	Libretto	A libretto is the text used in an extended musical work such as an opera, operetta, masque, oratorio, cantata, or musical. The term "libretto" is also sometimes used to refer to the text of major liturgical works, such as Mass, requiem, and sacred cantata, or even the story line of a ballet.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6f/Libretto_Cover_Andrea_Chenier.jpg/220px-Libretto_Cover_Andrea_Chenier.jpg
